text: Before software can be reusable it first has to be usable.
author: Ralph Johnson

text: There are 10 kinds of people in this world: those who understand binary and those who don’t.
author: Anonymous

text: One of the best programming skills you can have is knowing when to walk away for a while.
author: Oscar Godson

text: There is always one more bug to fix.
author: Ellen Ullman

text: Computers are fast; developers keep them slow.
author: Anonymous

text: Success is walking from failure to failure with no loss of enthusiasm.
author: Winston Churchill

text: Success is simple. Do what’s right, the right way, at the right time.
author: Arnold H. Glasgow

text: A strong, positive self-image is the best possible preparation for success.
author: Joyce Brothers

text: Celebrate what you’ve accomplished, but raise the bar a little higher each time you succeed.
author: Mia Hamm

text: Every sunrise brings a new opportunity to shine; embrace it with open arms.
author: Uncommon Quotes

text: Every setback is a setup for a comeback; resilience is your superpower.
author: Uncommon Quotes

text: You are a masterpiece in progress; appreciate the beauty of your evolution.
author: Uncommon Quotes

text: Your smile is a powerful tool; use it to brighten someone else’s day.
author: Uncommon Quotes

text: Good code is its own best documentation.
author: Steve McConnell

text: Programs must be written for people to read, and only incidentally for machines to execute.
author: Harold Abelson

author: Martin Fowler

author: John Johnson

text: The best way to predict the future is to invent it.
author: Alan Kay

text: Experience is the name everyone gives to their mistakes.
author: Oscar Wilde

text: Code is like humor. When you have to explain it, it’s bad.
author: Cory House
